  "text": "The ground ULF indices S gr and T gr are created from measurements from ground-based magnetometers in the 5-15 LT sector (dawnside and dayside) and in the 60°-70°region of magnetic latitude in the Northern Hemisphere. The geosynchronous ULF indices S geo and T geo are created from magnetic field measurements on board the GOES spacecraft [CITATION_1] in geosynchronous orbit (6.6 R E ) in the equatorial magnetosphere.",
